<Folder><name>Waypoints</name><Placemark><name>Hveragerði</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-21.185000,64.004000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Selfoss</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-20.997000,63.933500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Hella</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-20.401100,63.834400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Hvolsvöllur</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-20.237000,63.751000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Seljalandsfoss</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-19.989000,63.615500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Skógafoss</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-19.511300,63.532000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Reynisfjara black beach</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-19.046900,63.405500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Vík í Mýrdal</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-19.008600,63.418700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Eldhraun lava field</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-18.085000,63.705000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Kirkjubæjarklaustur</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-18.044000,63.790500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Skaftafell</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-16.975900,64.016600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Jökulsárlón glacier lagoon</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-16.181000,64.048000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Diamond Beach</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-16.182000,64.042000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Seljalandsfoss</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[60 m waterfall you can walk all the way around — there's a path behind the curtain of water. Get wet. Bring a waterproof for the camera.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-19.989000,63.615500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Skógafoss</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[60 m, 25 m wide. A staircase climbs the east side to a top viewing platform; the Fimmvörðuháls trail up to the volcano starts here.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-19.511300,63.532000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Reynisfjara</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Black-sand beach with hexagonal basalt columns and the Reynisdrangar sea-stacks offshore (legendary trolls turned to stone by the dawn). DANGEROUS sneaker waves; stay well back from the water.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-19.046900,63.405500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Eldhraun lava field</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Velvet-green moss carpets the lava from the 1783–84 Laki eruption, the largest known basalt flow in human history. Stay on marked paths — the moss is fragile and slow-growing.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-18.085000,63.705000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Skaftafell / Svínafellsjökull</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Glacier tongue you can walk to the foot of (with a guide for ice walks). The peak Hvannadalshnúkur (2,110 m) is Iceland's highest. Used as filming location in Interstellar.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-16.975900,64.016600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Jökulsárlón</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Iceberg-filled lagoon where the Breiðamerkurjökull glacier calves into the sea. Ice has darkened over 1,000 years of compression; the blue color is from light absorption. Boat tours weave through the bergs.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-16.181000,64.048000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Diamond Beach</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Across the road from Jökulsárlón. Icebergs that have drifted out of the lagoon wash up on black sand — translucent ice on jet sand looks like jewelry on velvet.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-16.182000,64.042000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
</Document></kml>
